This tool provides five automatic corrections that can improve a picture in most cases. therefore, use it before attempting any further manual processing.
The functions normalize, balance, automatic balance and contrast extend from the menu Correcting Automatic correction to automatically make the most of your colors. you will need to experiment with these effects to see which works best with your photo.
Normalize: this method scales the denier values over the entire image so that the darkest point is black and the brightest point is as bright as possible without changing its color shade. this function is often a magic correction for images that are dark or washed out.
Compare: this method adjusts the intensity channel of the selected image so that the histogram of the intensity channel is as flat as possible. sometimes the comparison results in very good results in improving the contrast of an image, sometimes it produces only garbage. it is a very powerful operation that causes either miracles in a picture or destroys it.
Automatic adjustment: this method maximizes the colour range in the red, green and blue channel. it determines the dark and light border tones and adjusts the red, green and blue channels to the complete histogram area.
Enhance contrast: this method improves the contrast and luminous intensity of the RGB values of an image by moving the lowest and highest values in the widest possible range and a new jib of all values in between. this is only visible with washed images and can be a good correction for bad photos.
