With & kphoto album; you can export a copy of your images to a .kim file. these can import others to your database. the image properties are imported with ex- and imported.
There are two different types of .kim files, internal and external. they differ in whether the images themselves are stored in the file or whether the file is only a link to images. the advantage of saving all images in the file is that you have all the pictures together and that you can share this file so independently. however, the obvious disadvantage is the file size.
You can either export a .kim file directly from the File menu... or along with HTML pages, see, create. if you create a .kim file along with an HTML file, this will be an external .kin file.
An external .kin file searches the images in two ways. first, it searches for the images that are in the folder of the .kim file. if the corresponding images are not found, the images of the URL you specified when creating the HTML files will be searched. this is of course only possible if you have created your .kin file using the HTML export.
