Raytracytracing is a Render method to produce a two-dimensional image of a three dimensional scene or model.
When you raytracen a scene, the renderer shoots hypothetical rays from the viewer's perspective (i.e. from the camera that renders the scenes) by each pixel in the scene. the render calculates how this ray is reflected by the objects and how atmospheric effects such as fog have effects. thus, the scene pixels are processed for pixel.
As you can imagine, you won't see anything without a camera, the camera is your eye with which you view the scene. without a light source you don't see anything, the picture is just black. obviously, every scene needs to be rendered, some light sources and at least one camera.
