This is because many programs write data as UTF-8 into the meta-information, but do not label it as Unicode. the following perl script fixes the problem.
#! / usr / bin / perl the "The file $ARGV [0] does not exist" unless -f $ARGV [0]; Mplib; my $v2tag = $mp3 > get _ v2tag; print "Error while writing the tags of $ARGV [0]\" unless $mp3 > set _ v2tag ($v2tag, amp; UTF8);
