& cdrdao;: this program burns audio or data CD-Rs in a run-through (also called disk-at-once mode or DAO) based on a textual description of the CD content (TOC file).
& cdrecord; / mkisofs;: burns all types of CD-Rs. & cdrecord; has all the features that also & cdrdao; therefore selects & k3b; usually automatically & cdrecord; for burning CDs. in some cases, & cdrecord; however, a higher quality with burned audio CDs.
Cdparanoia: a program for reading digital audio from a CD (CDDA - Compact Disc Digital Audio).
OGG Vorbis is a completely open, patented and professional audio encoding technology and for dealing with audio data streams. OGG Vorbis profits from Open Source and is in direct competition to MP3. this library is used by the Ogg Vorbis decoder and encoder modules.
Mad: this is a high-quality MPEG Audio decoder. it currently supports MPEG-1, MPEG-2 and MPEG 2.5. all three audio layers Layer I, Layer II, and Layer III (e.g. MP3) are fully supported. this library is used by the MP3 Decoder module.
Lame: a well developed MP3 Decoder, which can compete in terms of quality and speed with commercial encoder. lame is used by the MP3 encoder module.
FLAC: a free open source codec for lossless audio compression and decompression. it is used by the FLAC decoder module and the external audio encoder module, so you can read and write FLAC files.
Libsndfile, ffmpeg, FLAC, Musepack Decoder: additional libraries for processing various audio formats. with ffmpeg, for example, it is possible to decrypt WMA files and then burn them to an audio CD. deco
SOX: a utility that can convert and convert between different audio formats. SOX is used by the SOX Audio Encoder module.
Trancode: a command line program for video editing. you need it if you want to read a DVD.
VCDIlean: a fully featured authoring system for editing, disassembling and analysing video CDs and Super Video CDs.
Unserialize: this tool is used to adjust the volume of music files to a standard stage. for example, this can be useful for creating mixed CD's and Mp3 collections; without normalising, the different recording levels of the different albums can lead to the irresistible effect that the music pieces are played differently.
EMovix: this is a very small Linux distribution. it contains the necessary software to start from CD and automatically play all videos in the base folder of the CD.
