In & quantaplus; the work area is divided into three areas: global, local and project-related. this distinction concerns a number of components in & quantaplus;.
Global elements are available for everyone who uses & quantaplus; everything that is marked as global is stored in the shared folder structure of & quantaplus; this allows the group of administrators to secure different tool slides, actions and patterns in the global tree, which are then available to everyone in a multi-user environment on the system.
Local elements represent a personal collection of web development tools for a single user. these are user-specific patterns and toolbars. local elements are stored in the user directory so that they can only use this user in person.
Project related elements are available only within a specific project. this can be anything from & CSS, patterns to toolbars with special actions specifically for the files of a particular project. simply said, this is the most constrained size. all elements are stored in the folder tree of the project, which embeds the joint use of special tools and patterns by all employees within the project.
