& kmag; is a screen saver. you can magnify with & kmag; a part of the screen, as if you read a magnifying glass for the print or the exact looking of a photo. this application is interesting for different users: this includes artists, web designers and people with visual impairment. this documentation should be a complete manual for use of & kmag.
& KOK; is a very powerful application that is constantly expanded to include new features. it is optimized for use on low-performance computers.
The main window of & kmag; displays the enlarged portion of the screen. the image that appears in the magnifying window is an enlarged portion of the screen and is referred to as a selection box below.
In the default setting, magnifies & cons the area around the mouse cursor as a mobile magnifying glass. alternatively, you can set a selected screen area in the magnifying window (selection window mode) or the surroundings of the mouse-pointer at the edge of the screen (eg; at the left edge of the screen).
If you want to avoid that the mouse pointer is displayed in the enlarged window, select the pointer mouse cursor. please note that & kmag; currently not able to recognize the shape of the mouse pointer. this is always the default node; / Qt; -mouse pointer.
In the selection window mode, you can customize the selection window to your own needs. you can move it with the arrow keys and mouse buttons and change its size. this can be done in the following way:
Move the mouse pointer in the magnifying window and keep the left mouse button pressed so you can capture and move the contents of the magnifier window. this also goes with the arrow keys.
If you additionally press the & Shift key or use the & MMB, you can move the selection window.
This combination allows you to change the size of the selection window. note that the upper left corner of the selection window will be fixed and only the lower right corner is to be moved.
& KOK; has a lot of features. you can send the enlarged picture directly to the printer, save to a file, paste it into the clipboard (to insert it later into other applications), rotate the picture and much more.
